/ This is an example of an arrangement of the characters in the memory
/ In this assignment, you have to convert the input alphabets to upper cases, and store them to the memory,
/ starting from memory location of InputString.
/ The delimiter can be any non-alphabetic character.
StringAddr, ADR InputString
InputString, HEX 06D    / 'm' (ASCII code)
             HEX 061    / 'a'
             HEX 072    / 'r'
             HEX 069    / 'i'
             HEX 065    / 'e'
             HEX 0    / delimiter
